purchase of subsidiary shares
on september1, 2014, 3m (via sumitomo 3m limited) purchased sumitomo electric industries,ltd.s 25 percent interest in 3ms consolidated sumitomo 3m limited subsidiary for 90 billion japanese yen. upon completion of the transaction, 3m owned 100 percent of sumitomo 3m limited. this transaction was recorded as a financing activity (purchase of noncontrolling interest) in the statement of cash flows.
in april2014, 3m purchased the remaining noncontrolling interest in a consolidated 3m subsidiary for an immaterial amount, which was classified as a financing activity (purchase of noncontrolling interest) in the consolidated statement of cash flows.
