the pension accumulated benefit obligation represents the actuarial present value of benefits based on employee service and compensation as of the measurement date and does not include an assumption about future compensation levels. the accumulated benefit obligation of the u.s. pension plans was $15.149 billion and $14.834 billion at december31, 2016 and 2015, respectively. the accumulated benefit obligation of the international pension plans was $6.058 billion and $5.773 billion at december31, 2016 and 2015, respectively.
